00:19:08,385 --> 00:19:14,530
From Dom Harris, I'm making a fast-paced top-down shooter and would love to make it as accessible

325
00:19:14,670 --> 00:19:15,351
as possible.

326
00:19:15,851 --> 00:19:20,355
I've got sliders to control game speed for people with slower reaction speeds.

327
00:19:20,675 --> 00:19:25,259
I've got made sure it's all color blindness friendly and works with a screen reader, that

328
00:19:25,299 --> 00:19:25,840
sort of thing.

329
00:19:26,180 --> 00:19:31,264
Is there anything else for this type of game, a top-down shooter, that you can suggest?

330
00:19:32,746 --> 00:19:34,367
Wow, that's a difficult question.

331
00:19:34,427 --> 00:19:36,048
It sounds like you covered a lot already.

332
00:19:36,569 --> 00:19:37,629
Those are really good starts.

333
00:19:38,350 --> 00:19:40,331
Make sure that when you're doing colorblind friendliness

334
00:19:40,471 --> 00:19:42,953
that you're picking something that will work with most people

335
00:19:43,013 --> 00:19:45,334
because human eyes vary a lot.

336
00:19:45,975 --> 00:19:47,896
So if you're using filters, for example,

337
00:19:48,016 --> 00:19:49,157
it may not cover everybody.

338
00:19:49,577 --> 00:19:51,118
That's true of almost anything you pick.

339
00:19:52,159 --> 00:19:54,260
So having brightness and contrast can help too.

340
00:19:54,721 --> 00:19:55,761
Contrast in particular.

341
00:19:56,242 --> 00:19:58,383
High contrast is great for people with low vision.

342
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:01,305
Low contrast is great for people with photosensitivity.

343
00:20:01,545 --> 00:20:02,346
So both matter.

344
00:20:03,516 --> 00:20:07,958
That's one thing to keep in mind. I do like the fact you have game speed in particular.

345
00:20:08,298 --> 00:20:11,659
Alternate controls and reduced button modes can be helpful, too.

