00:23:39,350 --> 00:23:41,331
Thank you both for asking this.

393
00:23:41,351 --> 00:23:44,551
I just want to make sure I asked it as best as I could.

394
00:23:46,112 --> 00:23:49,672
How do you get people, whether it's developers or gamers,

395
00:23:49,712 --> 00:23:51,673
to buy in on accessibility mattering?

396
00:23:55,273 --> 00:23:57,574
I will point out that there's such a thing as a vocal minority.

397
00:23:58,134 --> 00:24:00,254
So keep that in mind when you're.

398
00:24:00,717 --> 00:24:05,000
working on feedback because the vocal minority tends to drown out the majority sometimes.

399
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:11,885
So it may not be as negative as you may think. Generally speaking, especially each following

400
00:24:11,945 --> 00:24:16,769
generation is more inclusive than the last. And Gen Z in particular just wants to know,

401
00:24:17,269 --> 00:24:23,494
why can't I play with my friends? So keep that in mind that it does often come from the right place

402
00:24:23,654 --> 00:24:27,797
and it's not as contentious as you may think. Now, when it comes to development,

403
00:24:28,666 --> 00:24:31,787
But I will point out the fact that this is using US census numbers.

404
00:24:32,668 --> 00:24:34,268
One in five people are disabled.

405
00:24:34,889 --> 00:24:36,989
When it comes to 18 plus, it's one in four.

406
00:24:37,390 --> 00:24:40,011
By the time you get to mid-70s, it's one in two.

407
00:24:40,511 --> 00:24:43,892
And statistically speaking, most people will be permanently disabled before they die.

408
00:24:44,693 --> 00:24:44,813
So.

409
00:24:45,587 --> 00:24:48,149
It affects a very, very large number of people,

410
00:24:48,390 --> 00:24:49,731
and gamers are aging.

411
00:24:50,051 --> 00:24:51,852
Yes, we have new gamers coming in all the time,

412
00:24:51,892 --> 00:24:53,914
but people, generally speaking, don't stop gaming.

413
00:24:54,654 --> 00:24:57,557
So that's just things to keep in mind when doing this,

414
00:24:58,297 --> 00:24:59,979
and that it is a large audience.

415
00:25:00,179 --> 00:25:02,341
And those numbers don't even count the one in 12 men

416
00:25:02,381 --> 00:25:03,141
who are colorblind.

417
00:25:03,702 --> 00:25:06,003
So when you're talking about these features,

418
00:25:06,564 --> 00:25:08,205
using the statistics can really help,

419
00:25:08,586 --> 00:25:10,927
explaining how it helps people can do.

420
00:25:10,947 --> 00:25:14,030
And I know that over half a million Madden users

421
00:25:14,070 --> 00:25:14,550
are colorblind.

422
00:25:15,132 --> 00:25:17,735
So when you come up with those numbers, and it's like, yeah,

423
00:25:17,755 --> 00:25:19,758
half a million people can't play your game adequately,

424
00:25:19,838 --> 00:25:21,480
and may not know that some of the UI is there,

425
00:25:22,301 --> 00:25:26,545
it becomes a lot easier to try to push things through.

426
00:25:27,086 --> 00:25:29,309
So I used a game jam to get started,

427
00:25:29,469 --> 00:25:32,312
and that's how I put in these features into Madden.

428
00:25:32,652 --> 00:25:33,373
And then I showed.

